  "text": "The CharField max_length validation spans five files: (1) django/db/models/fields/__init__.py contains the model CharField which validates max_length is a positive integer via _check_max_length_attribute() and adds MaxLengthValidator to enforce the length constraint at the field level. (2) django/core/validators.py defines MaxLengthValidator, the shared validator used by both model and form CharField. (3) django/db/backends/mysql/validation.py contains MySQL-specific backend enforcement that warns when unique CharFields exceed max_length 255. (4) django/forms/fields.py contains the form CharField which accepts max_length and adds MaxLengthValidator. (5) django/db/migrations/autodetector.py contains generate_altered_fields() which detects changes (including max_length changes) by deep-deconstructing old and new fields and generates AlterField operations when differences are found.",
